[0.001, "o", "\u001b[0mMass-energy curves spacetime geometry. Clocks closer to a massive object tick slower because they traverse a\r\nshorter path through the time dimension of curved spacetime — this is gravitational time dilation, described by\r\nthe Schwarzschild metric: Δt_far = Δt_near / √(1 - 2GM/rc²).\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\r\n"]
[1.718, "o", "\u001b[?25h"]
